## The setup

This post lives at `content/posts/hello-world.json`. It's a flat JSON file in the @webhouse/cms format. **PHP reads it directly** via the `Webhouse\Cms\Reader` class — no API calls, no database, just `glob()` and `json_decode()`.

## Laravel compatible

The `src/Reader.php` file is a single class with zero framework dependencies. To use it in a Laravel app, register it as a singleton service:

```php
// app/Providers/AppServiceProvider.php
public function register(): void {
    $this->app->singleton(\Webhouse\Cms\Reader::class, fn() =>
        new \Webhouse\Cms\Reader(base_path('content'))
    );
}
```

Then inject it into your controllers via constructor injection.
